## Step 1: Calculate Return on Equity (ROE)
ROE = Net Income / Shareholders' Equity × 100%

- Net Income = $1,193,771.08 (from income statement)
- Shareholders' Equity = $14,193,771.08 (from balance sheet, end amount of Total Owner's Equity)

ROE = $1,193,771.08 / $14,193,771.08 × 100% = 8.41%

## Step 2: Calculate Debt to Asset Ratio
Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets

- Total Liabilities = $829,755.77 (from balance sheet, end amount of Total Current Liabilities)
- Total Assets = $15,023,526.85 (from balance sheet, end amount of Total Assets)

Debt to Asset Ratio = $829,755.77 / $15,023,526.85 = 0.06

## Step 3: Calculate Gross Profit Margin
Gross Profit Margin = Gross Profit / Total Revenue × 100%

- Gross Profit = $2,610,115.02 (from income statement)
- Total Revenue = $5,695,115.02 (from income statement)

Gross Profit Margin = $2,610,115.02 / $5,695,115.02 × 100% = 45.83%
